<article>
    <h1>LONGCHAMP X POKE&#xAD;MON</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201009/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-09"><time>2020-10-09</time></a>
        - <span>STYLE LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Who’s that Poke­mon? None other than the Ja­panese video game crea­ture Pikachu which graces Longchamp’s iconic Le Pliage bag in the French lux­ury brand’s lat­est col­lab­o­ra­tion.</p>
    <p>Launch­ing in Longchamp stores next Tues­day, the bag is avail­able in four ex­clu­sive ver­sions, in­clud­ing one in black can­vas sport­ing a spe­cially de­signed Pikachu wear­ing a jockey’s hel­met, to pay homage to the Longchamp logo.</p>
    <p>Longchamp has a colour­ful his­tory of col­lab­o­ra­tors that in­clude Amer­i­can fash­ion de­signer Jeremy Scott and Chi­nese fash­ion blog­ger Mr Bags. On this col­lab­o­ra­tion, artistic di­rec­tor of Mai­son Longchamp, Ms Sophie De­la­fontaine, said: “We hadn’t ex­plored en­ter­tain­ment and gam­ing be­fore. It’s a very in­spir­ing world.”</p>
    <p>Prices range from $100 to</p>
    <p>$1,640.</p>

